  "response": "In most engineering colleges, getting a grace mark or being allowed to proceed to the next semester depends on several factors:\n\n1. Number of KTs (Backlog subjects)\n2. College rules and policies\n3. University regulations\n\nGenerally:\n- One KT might allow you to get grace or continue to next semester\n- Some colleges allow 2-3 KTs without stopping progression\n- You may need to clear the KT in the next available exam\n\nBest steps:\n1. Check your college's specific academic rules\n2. Consult your academic advisor or department head\n3. Verify university guidelines\n4. Prepare to clear the KT in upcoming exams\n\nRecommendation: Meet your college administration directly for precise information about your specific situation.",
